# Fix Missing Content Across All Pages (except index.html)

After auditing every page and the stylesheet, I found **3 root causes** for sections appearing blank:

## Root Causes

### 1. Missing CSS for `.timeline`, `.faq-container`, `.faq-toggle`
The service pages (llc-formation, bank-assistance, itin-application, us-phone) use classes like `.timeline`, `.timeline-step`, `.timeline-dot`, `.timeline-content`, `.faq-container`, and `.faq-toggle` — **but [style.css](file:///Users/tahmidnur/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/theresidentialaddress/style.css) has NO styles for these classes**. The CSS only defines `.zigzag-timeline` and `.faq-list`/`.faq-item` (different class names from what index.html uses). This means timelines and FAQ sections render as unstyled HTML with no visual layout.

### 2. `fade-up` animation elements stuck at `opacity: 0`
The CSS `.fade-up` class sets `opacity: 0` by default. The `.visible` class (added by an IntersectionObserver script) transitions elements to `opacity: 1`. However, **4 of the service pages only have a basic scroll header script** — they're missing the IntersectionObserver JS. This makes all `.fade-up` elements permanently invisible (testimonials, timeline steps, FAQ items, bento cards).

### 3. [us-address-service.html](file:///Users/tahmidnur/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/theresidentialaddress/us-address-service.html) is a broken Tailwind prototype
This page uses Tailwind CDN, a completely different design language, broken `<html>` structure, placeholder links, and doesn't match the site.

## Proposed Changes

### CSS — Adding Missing Styles

#### [MODIFY] [style.css](file:///Users/tahmidnur/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/theresidentialaddress/style.css)
Add CSS rules for the following missing classes used by the service pages:
- `.timeline` — vertical timeline container
- `.timeline-step` — individual step layout (flex, with left dot + right content)
- `.timeline-dot` — numbered circle on the left
- `.timeline-content` — text block on the right
- `.faq-container` — wrapper for FAQ items (max-width centered)
- `.faq-toggle` — the `+/-` toggle span inside `.faq-question`

Also add a vertical connecting line between timeline dots via `::before` pseudo-element on `.timeline`.

---

### JS — Adding IntersectionObserver + FAQ Toggle Script

#### [MODIFY] [llc-formation.html](file:///Users/tahmidnur/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/theresidentialaddress/llc-formation.html)
#### [MODIFY] [bank-assistance.html](file:///Users/tahmidnur/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/theresidentialaddress/bank-assistance.html)
#### [MODIFY] [itin-application.html](file:///Users/tahmidnur/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/theresidentialaddress/itin-application.html)
#### [MODIFY] [us-phone.html](file:///Users/tahmidnur/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/theresidentialaddress/us-phone.html)

Replace the minimal `<script>` section at the bottom of each page with the full script block that includes:
1. Header scroll effect (already present)
2. **IntersectionObserver** for `.fade-up` elements → adds `.visible` class
3. **FAQ accordion toggle** — clicking `.faq-question` toggles `.open` on parent `.faq-item`

